traceability-analytics.keyInsights: Footwear traceability analysis reveals high tariff policy risk for products sourced from Vietnam and China, affecting 68% of your footwear supply chain. Current origin traceability stands at 82%, with synthetic materials showing 95% traceability compared to leather at 71%. Recent policy changes indicate potential 15-25% tariff increases on footwear imports from these regions. Consider diversifying suppliers to Thailand and Indonesia where tariff risks are significantly lower and traceability compliance exceeds 90%.
